    # [Scene: Tide Research Station | Late Afternoon — Two Weeks After the Vote]

    scene bg ch12_f99e88_1 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: A taut, sustained string; undercurrent of urgent percussion]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Keyboard clicks, muted chatter, the distant swell of the sea]
    "Narration:"
    "Maya Serrin watch the live feed populate the wall: wave height, anchor tension, turbidity spikes, and the little green dots that mark volunteer teams out on the shore. Nyla's thumbnail scrolls through a raw CSV the"
    "way a surgeon reads a chart. Her grin is all teeth and algae-streaked fingertips — fierce and exhausted."
    "It is a victory written in tiny, bureaucratic fonts. Binding clauses. Citizen oversight. Audit trails that will not let a corporate ledger hide losses. Maya Serrin taste it like metal at the back of your throat,"
    "the same as when you open a stitch and find old salt in the wound."
    show nyla_torres at left:
        zoom 0.7

    nyla_torres "We pushed it live. All feeds. Time-stamped. Public archive."
    "She taps the screen; the URLs flash in sequence."

    nyla_torres "No dead zones. Mayor signed them into the emergency ordinance. We've got auditors queued for Monday."
    show maya_serrin at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_serrin "You published the anchor placements too?"
    "Your voice is neutral, because neutral is what holds when everything feels like it could shatter."

    nyla_torres "Every anchor, every dredge permit, the contractor manifests. We blurred a couple of addresses, but—"
    "She exhales."

    nyla_torres "—we made it available to anyone who'll check the data. The volunteers logged the GPS stamps as they installed the markers. People saw it happen."
    "Narration:"
    "Her words feed a quick, bright flare of relief through Maya Serrin — then Maya Serrin remember the meetings, Dr. Elena Park's terse nods, the legal phrasing you spent nights carving with Mayor Hale's dead-ink pen."
    "Maya Serrin remember bargaining for enforceable protections: defined fishing lanes; penalties written so precisely they cut; third-party auditors appointed by a citizen board. The community will have teeth where it once had only language."
    "Nyla hums under her breath, translating clauses into the plain language posts they'll stream to the town tomorrow. Volunteers at the back are already lining up to man a 24/7 monitoring station. For once, Maya Serrin feel the momentum of something larger than a single schedule."

    menu:
        "Praise Nyla openly":
            "You reach across the console and squeeze her shoulder. 'You did it,' you say. Nyla's shoulders drop a fraction; she lets the relief leak out as a laugh that is almost a sob."
        "Keep the mood tight, ask about vulnerabilities":
            "You narrow your eyes at the feed. 'Show me the weak points. Where will the model fail?' Nyla taps the screen again, the smile gone, and the lab fills with the sound of calculations being made aloud."

    # --- merge ---
    "The conversation continues."

    nyla_torres "It's not invincible."
    "She leans back against the counter."

    nyla_torres "The clauses are tight, Maya. But models are just that. Models don't take surprises like… sediment shifts into account easily. They don't feel wooden hulls rubbing against jagged sandbars."

    maya_serrin "I know."
    "You should feel elated. Instead, you feel the old, soft ache of responsibility arrange itself under your ribs."
    # [Scene: Community Hall | Evening — Emergency Ratification Session]
    hide nyla_torres
    hide maya_serrin

    scene bg ch12_f99e88_2 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Low, insistent drums; heartbeat-like]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Murmurs, the rustle of paper, a far-off gull]
    "Narration:"
    "Mayor Hale unfolds his folder with hands that no longer tremble but no longer hide the strain. The hall is packed — fishers in oilskins, elders with canes, volunteers with rain-streaked hair. Cameras from local media angle like flies. Maya Serrin feel every set of eyes as an added weight."
    show mayor_jerome_hale at left:
        zoom 0.7

    mayor_jerome_hale "This council binds the action plan and the oversight board to the construction contract. Any deviation requires a public hearing. Elena, your firm pledges to immediate remediation funds should displacement occur."
    show dr_elena_park at right:
        zoom 0.7

    dr_elena_park "We agreed to an escrow and independent auditors. We will fund relocation of mooring lines to maintain access. We are also offering funding for wetland restoration to mitigate long-term erosion."
    show maya_serrin at center:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_serrin "And enforcement?"
    "Your question leaves no room for softness."

    dr_elena_park "The auditors will have investigative authority. Missed performance metrics trigger fines directly wired into the escrow. We accept civilian watchdog status as a precondition."
    "Narration:"
    "There is a moment — a white-hot, brittle moment — where the room inhales together. This is what Maya Serrin worked for: enforceable conditions, transparent data, community representation with legal teeth. You could close your notebook and breathe."
    "Nyla hums under her breath, translating clauses into the plain language posts they'll stream to the town tomorrow. Volunteers at the back are already lining up to man a 24/7 monitoring station. For once, Maya Serrin feel the momentum of something larger than a single schedule."

    mayor_jerome_hale "We move forward. We move together."
    hide mayor_jerome_hale
    show aiden_koa at left:
        zoom 0.7

    aiden_koa "Together doesn't mean the waters forget how they move."
    "His jaw is set; Maya Serrin see the lines of the sea carried there."
    "Maya Serrin exchange a look with him — more whole than a sentence can hold. He nods just once, the gesture a contract of its own."
    # [Scene: Quay | Night — Community Mobilization]
    hide dr_elena_park
    hide maya_serrin
    hide aiden_koa

    scene bg ch12_f99e88_3 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Increasing tempo; percussion sharpens into frantic rhythm]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Distant thunder, chains creaking, waves punching the cofferdam]
    "Narration:"
    "Maya Serrin stand on the quay as volunteers map the freshly defined fishing lanes with reflective buoys and GPS tags. The engineered segments — Dr. Elena Park's firm’s concrete panels — lock together like a teeth-guard."
    "Behind them, living dunes are being reconstructed: truck loads of native cordgrass and strategically placed coir logs. It is, for a breath, a choreography of human intent."
    "Nyla's tablet pings a live alert: an offshore system shows a low-pressure bubble deepening faster than predicted. Maya Serrin feel it before the words finish scanning: the sky has the wrong color to it, a hard, bruised violet that sucks the warmth away."
    show nyla_torres at left:
        zoom 0.7

    nyla_torres "Storm's coming in faster. Models updated; it's steepening off the shelf. We should batten down personally, activate the volunteers' rotation."
    show maya_serrin at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_serrin "Alert the auditors. Make sure the salvage crews have priority access lanes. Notify the co-op — Aiden should be—"
    "Your voice cuts as a raven of prickle raises along your arms."
    show aiden_koa at center:
        zoom 0.7

    aiden_koa "I'm already sorting lines."
    "He moves with the economy of someone who has lived with the motion of the sea for decades."

    aiden_koa "But Maya Serrin—"
    "He looks at the concrete wall and then at the buoy markers."

    aiden_koa "These walls will work for surge. They won't stop everything."
    "Narration:"
    "Maya Serrin double-check the clauses in your head: defined thresholds, emergency triggers, mandatory remediation. The legal scaffolding is strong, a lattice designed to prevent the kind of behind-the-curtain choices that once cost neighbors their boats. But law bends against the brute geometry of water."

    menu:
        "Order everyone off the water now":
            "You shout the command. Volunteers move like a single animal. The quay clears, lights flash, and Aiden slams the hatch with a face like stone — relief, guilt, gratitude in messy layers."
        "Let fishers make the call; prioritize documentation instead":
            "You tell Nyla to keep the feeds rolling and let the captains decide. Aiden's look goes flat; he grips the rail until his knuckles blanch, the silence between you heavy and complicated."

